HEADWORD: Indubious
<hw>In*du"bi*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>indubius</ets>. See <er>In-</er> not, and
<er>Dubious</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Not dubious or doubtful; certain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not doubting; unsuspecting.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Indubious</xex> confidence.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Harvey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>indubitability</ent>⟦br⟧
